OL,3,CThe men taking part in group sessions
OL,4,Cfor self-confessed domestic abusers
OL,6,FEvery week in a room in Rotherham, a
OL,7,Fgroup of men come together to share
OL,8,Fopenly how they have abused their
OL,9,Fpartners.
OL,11,FSome admit they have been violent,
OL,12,Fothers have used more insidious
OL,13,Fmethods of manipulation to coerce and
OL,14,Fcontrol women.
OL,16,FAll of them say they have a desire to
OL,17,Fchange.
OL,19,F"I was controlling with money, I was
OL,20,Fdomineering, it was my way or no way,"
OL,21,Fone man tells me.
OL,26,@{D@AOU
